UPDATED:When a cell selected into the preliminary E-DCH active set is not included in the final E-DCH active set because the cell does not satisfy the E-DCH active set acceptance condition "CPICHEcNoNonEDCHNCell < CPICHEcNoEDCHServingCell + EDCHAddEcNoOffset".

kpi_info.title: DL_DCH_SEL_HSDPA_POWER_INT (M1002C521)
kpi_info.use: The number of times when the HS-DSCH downlink transport channel cannot be selected for an interactive class connection due to downlink power limits. UPDATED:When the HS-DSCH cannot be selected as a downlink transport channel due to PtxTotal>PtxTargetHSDPA or PtxNC>PtxTargetHSDPA conditions.

kpi_info.title: DL_DCH_SEL_HSDPA_POWER_BGR (M1002C522)

UPDATED:When a HS-DSCH cannot be selected as a downlink transport channel due to PtxTotal>PtxTargetHSDPA or PtxNC>PtxTargetHSDPA conditions.

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_EDCH_UE_INT (M1002C523)
kpi_info.use: The number of E-DCH setup failures due to UE for interactive class connections. UPDATED:When the RNC has received an RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION FAILURE / RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP FAILURE message from the UE during the E-DCH setup or a timer waiting for an RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE / RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP COMPLETE message expires. The counter is also updated if a UE in PCH state does not respond to paging when a direct PCH to DCH transition is attempted.

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_EDCH_UE_BGR (M1002C524)
kpi_info.use: The number of E-DCH setup failures due to UE for background class connections. UPDATED:When the RNC has received an RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION FAILURE / RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP FAILURE message from the UE during the E-DCH setup or a timer waiting for an RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE / RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP COMPLETE message expires. The counter is also updated if a UE in PCH state does not respond to paging when a direct PCH to DCH transition is attempted.

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_EDCH_BTS_INT (M1002C525)
kpi_info.use: The number of E-DCH setup failures due to BTS for interactive class connections. UPDATED:When the RNC receives NBAP: RADIO LINK RECONFIGURATION FAILURE or NBAP: RADIO LINK SETUP FAILURE message during the E-DCH setup, or when a timer waiting for the acknowledgement message expires. An exception to this is when the BTS returns failure cause "Transport resources Unavailable". It is counted into "due to transport" failure counter instead because the BTS uses that cause to indicate uplink transport congestion when IP-based Iub is used.

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_EDCH_BTS_BGR (M1002C526)
kpi_info.use: The number of E-DCH setup failures due to BTS for background class connections. UPDATED:When the RNC receives NBAP: RADIO LINK RECONFIGURATION FAILURE or NBAP: RADIO LINK SETUP FAILURE message during the E-DCH setup, or when a timer waiting for the acknowledgement message expires. An exception to this is when the BTS returns failure cause "Transport resources Unavailable". It is counted into "due to transport" failure counter instead because the BTS uses that cause to indicate uplink transport congestion when IP-based Iub is used.

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_EDCH_TRANS_INT (M1002C527)
kpi_info.use: The number of E-DCH setup failures due to transport for interactive class connections. UPDATED:When the E-DCH setup fails due to an Iub transport resource allocation failure.

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_EDCH_TRANS_BGR (M1002C528)
kpi_info.use: The number of E-DCH setup failures due to transport for background class connections. UPDATED:When the E-DCH setup fails due to an Iub transport resource allocation failure.

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_EDCH_OTHER_INT (M1002C529)

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_EDCH_OTHER_BGR (M1002C530)

kpi_info.title: ALLO_SUCCESS_EDCH_BGR (M1002C532)

kpi_info.title: ALLO_DUR_EDCH_INT (M1002C533)

kpi_info.title: ALLO_DUR_EDCH_BGR (M1002C534)

kpi_info.title: REL_EDCH_OTHER_FAIL_BGR (M1002C542)

kpi_info.title: LOAD_AMR_DGR_SF256_SUCCESS (M1002C564)

kpi_info.title: ALLO_HS_DSCH_RET_128_STR (M1002C572)

kpi_info.title: ALLO_DUR_HS_DSCH_FLOW_STR (M1002C573)

kpi_info.title: ALLO_DUR_HS_DSCH_RET_16_STR (M1002C574)

kpi_info.title: ALLO_DUR_HS_DSCH_RET_64_STR (M1002C575)

kpi_info.title: ALLO_DUR_HS_DSCH_RET_128_STR (M1002C576)

kpi_info.title: REL_ALLO_NORM_HS_DSCH_STR (M1002C578)

kpi_info.title: REL_ALLO_OTH_FAIL_HSDSCH_STR (M1002C579)
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH allocation releases due to other than radio link failure in the SRNC for streaming class connections. kpi_info.title: REL_ALLO_HS_DSCH_MOB_DCH_STR (M1002C580)

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_IUB_MAC_D_STR (M1002C582)

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_UE_HS_DSCH_STR (M1002C583)
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH setup failures due to UE in the SRNC for streaming class connections. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_BTS_HS_DSCH_STR (M1002C584)

UPDATED:When the setup of Iub transport resources fails for either the MAC-d flow or the return channel. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_16_IUB_HSDSCH_STR (M1002C586)
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH setup failures due to the 16 kbps return channel Iub transport for streaming traffic class connections. UPDATED:The counter is updated by one when the setup of Iub transport resources fails for the 16 kbps return channel. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_64_IUB_HSDSCH_STR (M1002C587)
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH setup failures due to the 64 kbps return channel Iub transport in the SRNC for streaming class connections. UPDATED:When the setup of Iub transport resources fails for the 64 kbps return channel. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_128_IUB_HSDSCH_ST (M1002C588)
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH failures due to the 128 kbps return channel Iub transport in the SRNC for streaming class connections. UPDATED:When the setup of Iub transport resources fails for the 128 kbps return channel. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: HS_DSCH_RET_UPGRADE_STR (M1002C589)
kpi_info.use: The number of DCH allocations with streaming class due to HSDPA return channel (DCH UL) upgrade. NOTE: Currently this counter is never updated because return channel upgrades are never performed on Streaming class connections. UPDATED:When the RNC has received an RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message from the UE - after successful HS-DSCH return channel upgrade. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: HS_DSCH_RET_DOWNGRADE_STR (M1002C590)
kpi_info.use: The number of DCH allocations with streaming class due to HSDPA return channel (DCH UL) downgrade. NOTE: Currently this counter is never updated because return channel downgrades are never performed on Streaming class connections. UPDATED:When the RNC has received an RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message from the UE - after successful HS-DSCH return channel downgrade. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: DCH_SEL_MAX_HSDPA_USERS_STR (M1002C591)
kpi_info.use: The number of times when the DCH channel type is selected for streaming class connections due to maximum amount of HSDPA users or MAC-d flows in the WBTS, local cell group or cell. The counter includes also HS-DSCH rejections due to temporary HSDPA user amount restriction applied by feature RAN2954. The counter is updated only in the initial user plane allocations, it is not updated if DCH x/y to HSDPA switch or serving cell change fails due to the maximum number of users reached. UPDATED: During the NRT channel type selection if the DCH channel type is selected due to maximum amount of HSDPA users or MAC-d flows in the WBTS, local cell group or cell. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: REL_ALLO_HS_DSCH_OTH_DCH_STR (M1002C592)
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH allocation normal releases due to other than mobility-related HS-DSCH to DCH switch (e.g. multi-RAB restrictions) for streaming class connections. UPDATED: When the user's HS-DSCH allocation is released due to other than mobility-related HS-DSCH to DCH switch. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: REL_ALLO_HS_DSCH_PRE_EMP_STR (M1002C593)
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH allocation normal releases due to pre-emptions for streaming class connections. UPDATED: When the user's HS-DSCH allocation is released due to pre-emption. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: REL_ALLO_RL_FAIL_HS_DSCH_STR (M1002C594)
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH allocation releases due to radio link failure, RLC protocol reset or uplink RLC unrecoverable error for streaming class connections. UPDATED: When the user's HS-DSCH allocation is released due to radio link failure, RLC protocol reset or uplink RLC unrecoverable error (Cell Update sent by UE). Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: REJ_HS_DSCH_AMR_STR (M1002C595)
kpi_info.use: The number of times that admission control rejects setting up an AMR + HS-DSCH connection for streaming class connections. UPDATED: When allocating AMR + HS-DSCH multi RAB is not possible because of admission control rejection. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_HS_DSCH_AMR_STR (M1002C596)
kpi_info.use: The number of setup failures for AMR + HS-DSCH for streaming class connections. UPDATED: When DCH or HS-DSCH setup fails and the result would have been AMR + HS-DSCH multi RAB. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_HS_DSCH_AMR_STR (M1002C597)
kpi_info.use: The number of AMR + HS-DSCH multi-RAB allocations for streaming class connections. UPDATED:When DCH or HS-DSCH mac-d flow setup is successful, and the result is AMR + HS-DSCH multi RAB. The counter is updated only if the previous configuration for the UE in the cell was not AMR+HS-DSCH, and the new configuration fulfills the criteria either after a new bearer allocation or due to mobility. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: REL_ALLO_NORM_HSDSCH_AMR_STR (M1002C598)
kpi_info.use: The number of AMR + HS-DSCH multi-RAB normal releases for streaming class connections (one of the RBs is released). UPDATED: When AMR + HS-DSCH multi RAB exists and either of the connections is released with normal cause. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: UL_DCH_SEL_MAX_HSUPA_USR_STR (M1002C599)
kpi_info.use: The number of times when the E-DCH uplink transport channel cannot be selected for a streaming class connection in this cell due to maximum amount of E-DCH users in the cell or in the local cell group. UPDATED:When the E-DCH cannot be selected as the uplink transport channel in this cell because the number of E-DCH users in the cell would exceed the limit defined by MaxNumberEDCHCell or the number of E-DCH users in local cell group would exceed MaxNumberEDCHLCG Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: UL_DCH_SEL_BTS_HW_STR (M1002C600)
kpi_info.use: The number of times when the E-DCH uplink transport channel cannot be selected for a streaming class connection in this cell because the BTS has reported that it has no capacity available for the E-DCH. UPDATED:When the E-DCH cannot be selected as the uplink transport channel in this cell because the BTS has reported with a RADIO RESOURCE MEASUREMENT REPORT message to be in a state where there is no capacity available for the E-DCH. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: EDCH_ALLO_CANC_NA_AS_STR (M1002C601)
kpi_info.use: The number of times when the E-DCH allocation made by the cell specific packet scheduler for a streaming class connection is cancelled due to a non-acceptable E-DCH active set. UPDATED:When a cell selected into the preliminary E-DCH active set is not included in the final E-DCH active set because the cell does not satisfy the E-DCH active set acceptance condition "CPICHEcNoNonEDCHNCell lt; CPICHEcNoEDCHServingCell + EDCHAddEcNoOffset". Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: DL_DCH_SEL_HSDPA_POWER_STR (M1002C602)
kpi_info.use: The number of times when the HS-DSCH downlink transport channel cannot be selected for a streaming class connection due to downlink power limits. UPDATED:When the HS-DSCH cannot be selected as a downlink transport channel due to PtxTotal>PtxTargetHSDPA or PtxNC>PtxTargetHSDPA conditions. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_EDCH_UE_STR (M1002C603)
kpi_info.use: The number of E-DCH setup failures due to UE for streaming class connections. UPDATED:When the RNC has received an RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION FAILURE / RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP FAILURE message from the UE during the E-DCH setup or a timer waiting for an RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE / RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP COMPLETE message expires. The counter is also updated if a UE in PCH state does not respond to paging when a direct PCH to DCH transition is attempted. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_EDCH_BTS_STR (M1002C604)
kpi_info.use: The number of E-DCH setup failures due to BTS for streaming class connections. UPDATED:When the RNC receives NBAP: RADIO LINK RECONFIGURATION FAILURE or NBAP: RADIO LINK SETUP FAILURE message during the E-DCH setup, or when a timer waiting for the acknowledgement message expires. An exception to this is when the BTS returns failure cause "Transport resources Unavailable". It is counted into "due to transport" failure counter instead because the BTS uses that cause to indicate uplink transport congestion when IP-based Iub is used. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_EDCH_TRANS_STR (M1002C605)
kpi_info.use: The number of E-DCH setup failures due to transport for streaming class connections. UPDATED: When the E-DCH setup fails due to an Iub transport resource allocation failure. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_EDCH_OTHER_STR (M1002C606)
kpi_info.use: The number of E-DCH setup failures for streaming class connections due to reasons not covered by the other failure counters, for example due to RNC internal failures. UPDATED: When the E-DCH setup fails due to some other reason that is not covered by the other failure counters. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_SUCCESS_EDCH_STR (M1002C607)
kpi_info.use: The number of successful E-DCH allocations for streaming class connections. UPDATED:When the RNC receives an RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE / RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP COMPLETE message from the UE after a successful E-DCH setup or upgrade from the DCH. The counter is updated also when the RNC receives an RRC: ACTIVE SET UPDATE COMPLETE message after a successful addition of a cell into the E-DCH active set. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_DUR_EDCH_STR (M1002C608)
kpi_info.use: The sum of E-DCH allocation durations for streaming class connections. UPDATED: This counter is updated with one-second sampling intervals during the E-DCH allocation time. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: REL_EDCH_NORM_STR (M1002C609)
kpi_info.use: The number of E-DCH normal releases in the SRNC for streaming class connections. UPDATED: When the E-DCH is released due to a normal cause, that is, not due to a failure. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: REL_EDCH_HSDSCH_SCC_STR (M1002C610)
kpi_info.use: The number of E-DCH releases due to a HS-DSCH serving cell change for streaming class connections, that is, when it is not possible to allocate E-DCH in the new HS-DSCH serving cell. M1002C609 is also updated along with this counter. UPDATED:When the E-DCH is released because of the HS-DSCH serving cell change. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: REL_EDCH_RL_FAIL_STR (M1002C611)
kpi_info.use: The number of E-DCH releases for streaming class connections due to a radio link failure, an uplink RLC unrecoverable error, or due to the UE not responding to an RRC message sent by the RNC. UPDATED: When the E-DCH is released due to a radio link failure, an uplink RLC unrecoverable error, or due to the UE not responding to an RRC message. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: REL_EDCH_OTHER_FAIL_STR (M1002C612)
kpi_info.use: The number of E-DCH releases for streaming class connections due to some other failure reason than a radio link failure or an uplink RLC unrecoverable error. UPDATED: When the E-DCH is released due to some other failure reason than a radio link failure or an uplink RLC unrecoverable error. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_HS_INTER_RNC_HHO_STR (M1002C613)
kpi_info.use: The number of successful HS-DSCH allocations for incoming Inter-RNC HHO for streaming class connections. Also counter M1002C569 is updated along with this counter. UPDATED:When the target-RNC of an Inter-RNC HHO has successfully allocated resources for an HS-DSCH user plane and sends RANAP: RELOCATION REQUEST ACKNOWLEDGE to the core network. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: STP_F_HS_INTER_RNC_HHO_STR (M1002C614)
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH setup failures for incoming Inter-RNC HHO for streaming class connections. Also one of the basic HS-DSCH setup failure counters is updated along with this counter. UPDATED: When the resource allocation for HS-DSCH user plane fails in the target-RNC of an inter-RNC HHO. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_ED_INTER_RNC_HHO_STR (M1002C615)
kpi_info.use: The number of successful E-DCH allocations for incoming Inter-RNC HHO for streaming class connections. UPDATED:When the target-RNC of an Inter-RNC HHO has successfully allocated resources for an HS-DSCH/E-DCH user plane and sends RANAP: RELOCATION REQUEST ACKNOWLEDGE to the core network. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: STP_F_ED_INTER_RNC_HHO_STR (M1002C616)
kpi_info.use: The number of E-DCH setup failures for incoming Inter-RNC HHO for streaming class connections. Also one of the basic E-DCH setup failure counters is updated along with this counter. UPDATED: When the resource allocation for HS-DSCH/E-DCH user plane fails in the target-RNC of an inter-RNC HHO. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_AMR_MULTINRT_HSPA (M1002C617)
kpi_info.use: The number of allocations for AMR + more than one NRT_HSPA. UPDATED:When either AMR is successfully established on top of HSPA or HSPA on top of AMR either as initial allocation or due to serving cell change. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_MULTINRT_HSPA (M1002C618)
kpi_info.use: The number of allocations for more than one NRT_HSPA. UPDATED:When HSPA is successfully established on top of another HSPA radio bearer either as initial allocation or due to serving cell change. The counter is updated if the UE has only NRT RABs. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_AMR_RT_NRT_HSPA (M1002C619)
kpi_info.use: The number of allocations for AMR + RT_HSPA + NRT_HSPA.UPDATED:When AMR or HSPA bearer is successfully established forming combination AMR + RT_HSPA + NRT_HSPA either as initial allocation or due to serving cell change. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_AMR_RT_MULTINRT_HSPA (M1002C620)
kpi_info.use: The number of allocations for AMR + RT_HSPA + more than one NRT_HSPA. UPDATED:When AMR or HSPA bearer is successfully established forming combination AMR + RT_HSPA + n*NRT_HSPA either as initial allocation or due to serving cell change. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_RT_NRT_HSPA (M1002C621)
kpi_info.use: The number of allocations for RT_HSPA + NRT_HSPA. UPDATED: When HSPA bearer is successfully established forming combination RT_HSPA + NRT_HSPA either as initial allocation or due to serving cell change. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_RT_MULTINRT_HSPA (M1002C622)
kpi_info.use: The number of allocations for RT_HSPA + more than one NRT_HSPA. UPDATED:When HSPA bearer is successfully established forming combination RT_HSPA + n*NRT_HSPA either as initial allocation or due to serving cell change. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_CM_HSDPA_IFHO (M1002C623)
kpi_info.use: The number of successful compressed mode allocations for HSDPA users triggered by inter-frequency measurements. UPDATED: When the compressed mode is successfully allocated for HSDPA user. This counter is updated for all active set cells, also in the DRNC. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_DURA_CM_HSDPA_IFHO (M1002C624)
kpi_info.use: The allocation duration of compressed mode for HSDPA users triggered by inter-frequency measurements. UPDATED: This counter is updated with a 1-second sampling interval during the compressed mode allocation time for all active set cells, also in the DRNC side. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: REJ_CM_HSDPA_IFHO (M1002C625)
kpi_info.use: The number of rejected compressed mode requests for HSDPA users triggered by inter-frequency measurements.UPDATED:When the admission control rejects the compressed mode request for HSDPA user. This counter can be updated in any active set cell, also on the DRNC side. The counter is also updated when Admission Control rejects HSUPA to HSDPA channel type switch request sent for making it possible to use HSDPA compressed mode. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: REJ_DCH_DUE_POWER_INT_UL (M1002C626)
kpi_info.use: The number of NRT DCH setup rejects for interactive traffic class due to power limits in UL. UPDATED:When admission control rejects interactive DCH setup due to power limits in UL. This counter includes initial DCH setups, handover attempts and channel type switches from E-DCH to DCH. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: REJ_DCH_DUE_POWER_BGR_UL (M1002C627)
kpi_info.use: The number of NRT DCH setup rejects for background traffic class due to power limits in UL. UPDATED:When admission control rejects background DCH setup due to power limits in UL. This counter includes initial DCH setups, handover attempts and channel type switches from E-DCH to DCH. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: REJ_DCH_REC_DUE_PWR_INT_UL (M1002C628)
kpi_info.use: The number of NRT DCH reconfiguration rejects for interactive traffic class due to power limits in UL. UPDATED:When admission control rejects interactive DCH reconfiguration due to power limits in UL. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: REJ_DCH_REC_DUE_PWR_BGR_UL (M1002C629)
kpi_info.use: The number of NRT DCH reconfiguration rejects for background traffic class due to power limits in UL. UPDATED:When admission control rejects background DCH reconfiguration due to power limits in UL. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: ATT_HS_DSCH_DRNC (M1002C630)
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH allocation attemps in DRNC. Includes initial allocations, channel type switches and serving cell changes. UPDATED:When the cell specific admission control entity in the DRNC receives a request to allocate HS-DSCH.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_HS_DSCH_DRNC (M1002C631)
kpi_info.use: The number of successful HS-DSCH resource allocations in DRNC. UPDATED:When the DRNC sends RNSAP: RADIO LINK RECONFIGURATION READY or RNSAP: RADIO LINK SETUP RESPONSE message to the SRNC after successful HS-DSCH allocation. It must be noted that at this phase the new configuration has not yet been signalled to the UE.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_DUR_HS_DSCH_DRNC (M1002C632)
kpi_info.use: HS-DSCH allocation duration in DRNC. This counter covers all traffic classes, the other HS-DSCH allocation duration counters are not updated by DRNC. UPDATED:Allocation duration counter is updated with a 1 second interval during the HS-DSCH allocation time.

kpi_info.title: ATT_EDCH_DRNC (M1002C633)
kpi_info.use: The number of E-DCH allocation attemps in DRNC. Includes initial allocations, channel type switches and soft handover branch additions. UPDATED:When the cell specific admission control entity in the DRNC receives a request to allocate E-DCH.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_EDCH_DRNC (M1002C634)
kpi_info.use: The number of successful E-DCH resource allocations in DRNC. UPDATED:When the DRNC sends RNSAP: RADIO LINK RECONFIGURATION READY, RNSAP: RADIO LINK SETUP RESPONSE or RNSAP: RADIO LINK ADDITION RESPONSE message to the SRNC after a successful E-DCH allocation. It must be noted that at this phase the new configuration has not yet been signalled to the UE.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_DUR_EDCH_DRNC (M1002C635)
kpi_info.use: E-DCH allocation duration in DRNC. This counter covers all traffic classes, the other E-DCH allocation duration counters are not updated by DRNC. UPDATED:Allocation duration counter is updated with a 1 second interval during the E-DCH allocation time.

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_BTS_HS_DSCH_AMR (M1002C636)
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH setup failures due to BTS or Iur for CS Voice call. UPDATED:When the RNC receives NBAP: RADIO LINK RECONFIGURATION FAILURE, NBAP: RADIO LINK SETUP FAILURE or RNSAP: RADIO LINK RECONFIGURATION FAILURE message during the transition to HS-DSCH or a timer waiting for the acknowledgement expires. An exception to this is when the BTS returns failure cause "Transport resources Unavailable". It is counted into DUE TO TRANSPORT failure counter instead.

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_UE_HS_DSCH_AMR (M1002C637)
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH setup failures due to UE for CS Voice call. UPDATED:When the RNC receives RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION FAILURE or RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP FAILURE during the HS-DSCH setup or a timer waiting for the UE acknowledgement expires.

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_TRANS_HS_DSCH_AMR (M1002C638)
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH setup failures due to transport for CS Voice call. UPDATED:When the CS Voice HS-DSCH setup fails due to Iub or Iur transport resource allocation failure. Note that in case of IP-based Iub this includes also the cases when the BTS returns NBAP failure cause "Transport resources Unavailable" in NBAP: RADIO LINK SETUP FAILURE or NBAP: RADIO LINK RECONFIGURATION FAILURE.

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_OTHER_HS_DSCH_AMR (M1002C639)
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH setup failures for CS Voice call due to reasons not covered by the other failure counters, for example due to RNC internal failures. UPDATED:When the CS Voice HS-DSCH setup fails due to some other reason that is not covered by the other failure counters.

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_BTS_EDCH_AMR (M1002C640)
kpi_info.use: The number of E-DCH setup failures due to BTS or Iur for CS Voice call. UPDATED:When the RNC receives NBAP: RADIO LINK RECONFIGURATION FAILURE, NBAP: RADIO LINK SETUP FAILURE or RNSAP: RADIO LINK RECONFIGURATION FAILURE message during the E-DCH setup or the timer waiting for the acknowledgement expires.

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_UE_EDCH_AMR (M1002C641)
kpi_info.use: The number of E-DCH setup failures due to UE for CS Voice call. UPDATED:When the RNC receives RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION FAILURE or RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP FAILURE during the E-DCH setup or a timer waiting for the UE acknowledgement expires.

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_TRANS_EDCH_AMR (M1002C642)
kpi_info.use: The number of E-DCH setup failures due to transport for CS Voice call. UPDATED:When the CS Voice E-DCH setup fails due to Iub or Iur transport resource allocation failure. Note that in case of IP-based Iub this includes also the cases when the BTS returns NBAP failure cause "Transport resources Unavailable" in NBAP: RADIO LINK SETUP FAILURE or NBAP: RADIO LINK RECONFIGURATION FAILURE.

kpi_info.title: SETUP_FAIL_OTHER_EDCH_AMR (M1002C643)
kpi_info.use: The number of E-DCH setup failures for CS Voice call due to reasons not covered by the other failure counters, for example due to RNC internal failures. UPDATED:When the CS Voice E-DCH setup fails due to some other reason that is not covered by the other failure counters.

kpi_info.title: REL_ALLO_NORM_HS_DSCH_AMR (M1002C644)
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH normal releases in the SRNC for CS Voice call. UPDATED:When the HS-DSCH allocation is released with normal cause.

kpi_info.title: REL_ALLO_RL_FAIL_HS_DSCH_AMR (M1002C645)
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH allocation releases due to radio link failure, Cell Update or RLC unrecoverable error for CS Voice call. UPDATED:When the user's HS-DSCH allocation is released due to radio link failure, Cell Update or RLC unrecoverable error.

kpi_info.title: REL_ALLO_OTH_FAIL_HSDSCH_AMR (M1002C646)
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH allocation releases due to other than radio link failure in the SRNC for CS Voice call. UPDATED:When the HS-DSCH allocation is released with a failure cause other than radio link failure.

kpi_info.title: REL_ALLO_NORM_EDCH_AMR (M1002C647)
kpi_info.use: The number of E-DCH normal releases in the SRNC for CS Voice call. UPDATED:When the E-DCH allocation is released with normal cause.

kpi_info.title: REL_ALLO_RL_FAIL_EDCH_AMR (M1002C648)
kpi_info.use: The number of E-DCH allocation releases due to radio link failure, Cell Update or RLC unrecoverable error for CS Voice call. UPDATED:When the user's E-DCH allocation is released due to radio link failure, Cell Update or RLC unrecoverable error.

kpi_info.title: REL_ALLO_OTH_FAIL_EDCH_AMR (M1002C649)
kpi_info.use: The number of E-DCH allocation releases due to other than radio link failure in the SRNC for CS Voice call. UPDATED:When the E-DCH allocation is released with a failure cause other than radio link failure.

kpi_info.title: SWI_R99_TO_HSPA_CS_VOICE (M1002C650)
kpi_info.use: The number of successful HSPA channel type switches from Rel99 to HS-DSCH/E-DCH for CS Voice call. UPDATED:When a UE acknowledges a successful channel type switch from Rel99 to HS-DCSH/E-DCH.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_EDCH_SRB_SRNC (M1002C664)
kpi_info.use: The number of successful E-DCH allocations for Signalling Radio Bearer in the SRNC. The downlink SRB channel type can be either Rel99 DCH or HS-DSCH. UPDATED:When the RNC receives RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message or other RRC protocol acknowledgement message from the UE after a successful E-DCH allocation for SRB. This can happen either in an initial allocation, soft handover branch addition, incoming hard handover or channel type switch.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_EDCH_SRB_DRNC (M1002C665)
kpi_info.use: The number of successful E-DCH resource allocations for Signalling Radio Bearer in the DRNC. The downlink SRB channel type can be either Rel99 DCH or HS-DSCH. Note that this does not still mean that the allocation would be successful from end user point of view. UPDATED:When the DRNC responds to the SRNC with RNSAP: RADIO LINK RECONFIGURATION READY, RNSAP: RADIO LINK SETUP RESPONSE or RNSAP: RADIO LINK ADDITION RESPONSE message after a successful E-DCH resource allocation for SRB.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_HS_DSCH_SRB_SRNC (M1002C666)

UPDATED:When the RNC receives RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message or other RRC protocol acknowledgement message from the UE after a successful HS-DSCH allocation for SRB. This can happen either in an initial allocation, serving cell change, incoming hard handover or channel type switch.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_DUR_HS_DSCH_INACTIV_BGR (M1002C668)
kpi_info.use: The sum of HS-DSCH MAC-d flow allocation durations in inactive state in the SRNC for background class connections. Counter M1002C397 is updated along with this counter, it includes both active and inactive allocation duration. UPDATED:The counter is updated with a 1-second sampling intervals during the HS-DSCH allocation time when a UE is in inactive state. The counter is not dependent on CPC feature but can be updated also for non-CPC UEs.

kpi_info.title: ATT_HSPA_DIREAL_BGR (M1002C672)
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH/E-DCH or HS-DSCH/DCH allocation attempts by Direct Resource Allocation for background traffic class. This counter is updated for the first cell that is attempted to make HS-DSCH serving cell. Possible attempts to other cells after a failure of the intial cell are not anymore counted and thus the counter is updated only once per RAB Assignment Request. UPDATED: When HS-DSCH/E-DCH or HS-DSCH/DCH user plane setup is triggered immediately upon receiving RANAP: RAB ASSIGNMENT REQUEST.

kpi_info.title: ATT_HSPA_DIREAL_INT (M1002C673)
kpi_info.use: The number of HS-DSCH/E-DCH or HS-DSCH/DCH allocation attempts by Direct Resource Allocation for interactive traffic class.This counter is updated for the cell that is attempted to make HS-DSCH serving cell. Possible attempts to other cells after a failure of the intial cell are not anymore counted and thus the counter is updated only once per RAB Assignment Request. UPDATED: When HS-DSCH/E-DCH or HS-DSCH/DCH user plane setup is triggered immediately upon receiving RANAP: RAB ASSIGNMENT REQUEST.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_SUCC_HSPA_DIREAL_BGR (M1002C674)
kpi_info.use: The number of successful HS-DSCH/E-DCH or HS-DSCH/DCH allocations with Direct Resource Allocation for background traffic class. This counter is updated for the HS-DSCH serving cell. In case of retries were done to multiple cells, attempt counter M1002C672 could have been updated to different cell than this allocation counter.Also counter M1002C389 is updated along with this counter. UPDATED: When the UE responds with RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP COMPLETE indicating a successful user plane setup.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_SUCC_HSPA_DIREAL_INT (M1002C675)
kpi_info.use: The number of successful HS-DSCH/E-DCH or HS-DSCH/DCH allocations with Direct Resource Allocation for interactive traffic class. This counter is updated for the HS-DSCH serving cell. In case of retries were done to multiple cells, attempt counter M1002C673 could have been updated to different cell than this allocation counter.Also counter M1002C385 is updated along with this counter. UPDATED: When the UE responds with RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP COMPLETE indicating a successful user plane setup.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_CM_HSUPA_IFHO (M1002C676)
kpi_info.use: The number of successful compressed mode allocations for HSUPA users triggered by inter-frequency measurements. Also M1002C623 is updated along with this counter. UPDATED: When the compressed mode is successfully allocated for HSUPA user. This counter is updated for all active set cells on SRNC side.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_DURA_CM_HSUPA_IFHO (M1002C677)
kpi_info.use: The allocation duration of compressed mode for HSUPA users triggered by inter-frequency measurements. Also M1002C624 is updated along with this counter. UPDATED: The counter is updated with a 1 second sampling interval during the compressed mode allocation time for all active set cells on SRNC side.

kpi_info.title: REJ_CM_HSUPA_IFHO (M1002C678)
kpi_info.use: The number of rejected compressed mode requests for HSUPA users triggered by inter-frequency measurements. Also M1002C625 is updated along with this counter. UPDATED: When the admission control rejects the compressed mode requests for HSUPA user. This counter is updated for all active set cells that cause the rejection.

kpi_info.title: TRAFFIC_SPARE_1 (M1002C679)
kpi_info.use: This is a spare counter for future purposes. UPDATED: Never.

kpi_info.title: TRAFFIC_SPARE_2 (M1002C680)
kpi_info.use: This is a spare counter for future purposes. UPDATED: Never.

kpi_info.title: SETUP_REJ_EDCH_AC_INT (M1002C681)
kpi_info.use: The number of E-DCH setup failures due to admission control for interactive class connections. UPDATED: When E-DCH cannot be setup due to uplink admission control rejection. This happens when the averaged estimated Rel99 interference exceeds the limit value defined as the maximum of the values of the management parameters PrxTarget, PrxTargetMax and PrxMaxTargetBTS. The counter is updated only for initial E-DCH allocation attempts, not for channel type switches or serving cell changes.

kpi_info.title: SETUP_REJ_EDCH_AC_BGR (M1002C682)
kpi_info.use: The number of E-DCH setup failures due to admission control for background class connections. UPDATED: When E-DCH cannot be setup due to uplink admission control rejection. This happens when the averaged estimated Rel99 interference exceeds the limit value defined as the maximum of the values of the management parameters PrxTarget, PrxTargetMax and PrxMaxTargetBTS. The counter is updated only for initial E-DCH allocation attempts, not for channel type switches or serving cell changes.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_HS_DSCH_FLOW_PTT (M1002C683)
kpi_info.use: The number of successful HS-DSCH allocations for PTT. Also M1002C385 or M1002C389 is updated along with this counter. UPDATED:When RNC has received RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message from PTT UE - after successful HS-DSCH MAC-d flow setup for PTT RAB

kpi_info.title: ALLO_SUCCESS_EDCH_PTT (M1002C684)
kpi_info.use: The number of successful E-DCH allocations for PTT. Also M1002C531 or M1002C532 is updated along with this counter. UPDATED:When RNC has received RRC: RADIO BEARER RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE / RRC: RADIO BEARER SETUP COMPLETE message from PTT UE - after successful E-DCH MAC-d flow setup for PTT RAB

kpi_info.title: MEH_RESTR_R99_UL_DCH (M1002C685)
kpi_info.use: The number of Rel99 UL DCH bitrate selections where the bitrate is restricted due to temporary maximum bitrate of Mass Event Handler feature being active. The restriction is triggered because the NRT scheduling queue length exceeded the threshold defined by WCEL-MEHQueueThreshold and WCEL-MEHLoadStateTtT. This counter specifically measures the selections of lower bitrate, regardless of whether the allocation was finally successful from the point-of-view of the UE and other network resource. UPDATED:This counter is updated when the cell specific admission control entity of the RNC selects restricted UL DCH bitrate due to due to exceeded

kpi_info.title: MEH_REJECT_EDCH (M1002C686)
kpi_info.use: The number of UL DCH selections instead of E-DCH selections due to Mass Event Handler temporary user amount restriction. The restriction is triggered because the NRT scheduling queue length exceeded the threshold defined by WCEL-MEHQueueThreshold and WCEL-MEHLoadStateTtT. UPDATED:This counter is updated when the cell specific admission control entity of the RNC does not allow E-DCH allocation due to temporary user amount restriction caused by due to exceeded scheduling queue length threshold. Also existing UL DCH SELECTED counters like M1002C515, M1002C516 are updated together with this new counter.

kpi_info.title: MEH_REJECT_HSDSCH (M1002C687)
kpi_info.use: The number of DL DCH selections instead of HS-DSCH due to Voice Call Priorization During High Traffic Load temporary user amount restriction. UPDATED:This counter is updated when the cell specific admission control entity of the RNC does not allow HS-DSCH allocation due to temporary user amount restriction applied by Voice Call Priorization During High Traffic Load feature. Also existing DL DCH SELECTED counters like M1002C475, M1002C476 are updated together with this new counter.

kpi_info.title: MEH_ADMIT_CS_VOICE (M1002C688)
kpi_info.use: The number of CS Voice calls admitted to the cell when (Ptx_nc + delta_Ptx_nc) is greater than PtxTarget. This special admission condition of Voice Call Priorization During High Traffic Load functionality triggers temporary restriction of HSDPA user amount. This counter specifically measures the successful admission control allocations for CS voice, regardless of whether the allocation was finally successful from the point-of-view of the UE and other network resource. UPDATED:This counter is updated when the cell specific admission control entity of the RNC admits CS Voice call to the cell.

kpi_info.title: MEH_REJECT_2MS_EDCH_TTI (M1002C689)
kpi_info.use: The number of times when E-DCH 2ms TTI allocation is prevented by the Mass Event Handler function because the number of HSUPA users has reached the WCELMEHHSUPAUserNbr2msTTI threshold. This Mass Event Handler action is also able to occur without M1000C406 and M1000407. UPDATED:This counter is updated when the cell specific admission control entity of the RNC decides to select 10 ms E-DCH TTI instead of 2 ms TTI due to due to high amount of HSUPA users.

kpi_info.title: SC_HSDPA_SEL_UL_LOAD (M1002C690)
kpi_info.use: The number of Single-Carrier HSDPA non-MIMO channel type selections instead of DC-HSDPA, MC-HSDPA or MIMO due to high uplink load. In RU40 release this counter was implemented as M1002C679 TRAFFIC_SPARE_1, but from RU50 onwards M1002C679 is not anymore updated. UPDATED: When the admission control rejects DC-HSDPA, MS-HSDPA or MIMO allocation due to high uplink load, and SC-HSDPA without MIMO is selected instead. The counter is updated for the selected HSDPA serving cell.

kpi_info.title: SC_HSUPA_SEL_UL_LOAD (M1002C691)
kpi_info.use: The number of Single-Carrier HSUPA channel type selections instead of DC-HSUPA due to high uplink load. The counter is updated in the cell where Single-Carrier E-DCH is selected after uplink load of either primary or secondary carrier has prevented DC-HSUPA selection. UPDATED: When the admission control rejects DC-HSUPA allocation due to high uplink load in primary or in secondary cell, and SC-HSUPA is selected instead.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_COM_LTE (M1002C692)
kpi_info.use: The number of successful allocations of compressed mode for LTE measurement with HSUPA (HS-DSCH/E-DCH), HSDPA (HS-DSCH/DCH) or Rel99 DCH (DCH/DCH) transport channel. Along with this counter, M1002C367, M1002C368, M1002C381, M1002C382, M1002C433-M1002C436, M1002C441-M1002C444 are also updated when applicable. In other words LTE ISHO is counted as ISHO in the legacy counters, and then the number of 2G ISHO can be calculated from the difference of LTE specific counter and the legacy counter. UPDATED:When the UE acknowledges compressed mode activation.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_DUR_COM_LTE (M1002C693)
kpi_info.use: Allocation duration of compressed mode for LTE measurement with HSUPA (HS-DSCH/E-DCH), HSDPA (HS-DSCH/DCH) or Rel99 DCH (DCH/DCH) transport channel. Along with this counter, M1002C369, M1002C370, M1002C383, M1002C384, M1002C437-M1002C440, M1002C446-M1002C449 are also updated when applicable. In other words LTE ISHO is counted as ISHO in the legacy counters, and then the number of 2G ISHO can be calculated from the difference of LTE specific counter and the legacy counter. UPDATED:Updated with 1 second intervals during compressed mode allocation for LTE measurement.

kpi_info.title: ALLO_AMR_122_74_59_475 (M1002C694)
kpi_info.use: The number of successful allocations of AMR codec mode set {12.2, 7.4, 5.9, 4.75}. The counter is updated by the Controlling-RNC of the cell. The same counter is used both in SRNC and DRNC role. UPDATED: When RNC admission control entity successfully allocates AMR codec mode set {12.2, 7.4, 5.9, 4.75} for a DCH. The counter is not updated if a failure happens and fallback to another codec set is performed.
